  JS CLASS OVERRIDES
  ------------------
  To override a FoxSell class, register a factory function on window.foxsell.overrides
  before this script tag. The factory receives the base class and must return a subclass.

  Available keys:
    foxsell-mix-match
    foxsell-product-card
    foxsell-category-header
    foxsell-variant-radio
    foxsell-variant-select

  Example:
    window.foxsell.overrides['foxsell-mix-match'] = (Base) => class extends Base {
      addToBundle(item, quantity, categoryId) {
        super.addToBundle(item, quantity, categoryId);
        console.log('Item added:', item);
      }
    };
